Summary: Two UFOs Emitting bursts of light
divs: Sighting DetailsAt 9:15 P.M. the witness was at home when a neighbor pounded on the door yelling that there were UFOs overhead. The witness grabbed her binoculars and ran out to see two objects, both round and red on the bottom but blue and white in the body. Both were emitting what appeared to be strobes of light which were ���crooked like lighting���. The objects moved in whirling, zig-zagging, and S movements as they advanced very slowly toward the west northwest. The smaller of the two objects, which seemed to be farther away, appeared to be over the Intercoastal Waterway. After 45 minutes, the objects were covered by clouds and were not visible to the witnesses.
